===Etymology===
[[Appendix:Glossary#loanword|Borrowing]] from {{bor|en|ja|琵琶|tr=biwa}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A plucked [[lute]], originating in the [[classical]] and [[traditional]] music of Japan, characterized by a pear-shaped body and four or five high frets, giving the instrument a distinctively [[twang]]y tone.

